Tanner Aus is a professional rodeo contestant known for his exceptional skills in bareback riding. Born and raised in Granite Falls, Minnesota, Aus has made a name for himself in the world of rodeo, earning multiple titles and accolades throughout his career. With a strong work ethic and dedication to the sport, Tanner Aus has become a prominent figure in the rodeo community.

Here you can follow Tanner Aus’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Tanner Aus

Tanner Aus was born near Granite Falls, Minnesota, and grew up in a family with a rodeo background. His father, John Aus, was a bareback rider who retired in 1998, and Tanner began his own rodeo journey the following year at the age of 9.

Tanner’s passion for rodeo grew as he competed in various events throughout his youth, eventually leading him to pursue a professional career in the sport.

Early Career

Tanner Aus started his rodeo career at a young age, competing in various youth and high school rodeo events. 

He later attended Iowa Central Community College and Missouri Valley College on rodeo scholarships, where he continued to hone his skills in bareback riding. 

In 2012, Tanner won the intercollegiate national championship in bareback riding while attending Missouri Valley College.

Professional Career

Tanner Aus is a professional rodeo cowboy specializing in bareback riding. He hails from Granite Falls, Minnesota, and has been a part of the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) since 2009.

His career in rodeo began at a young age, following in the footsteps of his father, a former bareback rider. Aus has had a successful career, qualifying for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (NFR) eight times.

He has competed in both large and small rodeos, with a focus on accumulating points based on his monetary winnings As of 2023, his career earnings stand at $1,479,062. In 2022, Aus finished 8th in the world standings and 13th in the Wrangler NFR standings.

Despite some challenges, he managed to earn nearly $80,000 at the Wrangler National Championship Rodeo event in Las Vegas. He also achieved a personal victory in 2023, winning at the Jaycee Bootheel Rodeo in Sikeston, Missouri, after nearly a dozen attempts.

Throughout his career, Aus has demonstrated resilience and determination. He has often had to make tough decisions, such as taking time off to recover from injuries or fatigue, but these choices have often led to successful returns.

Tanner Aus’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Tanner Aus’s net worth is estimated to be $3 million.

Career Earnings

Tanner Aus, a professional rodeo cowboy, has had a successful career with significant earnings. As of 2023, his career earnings stand at $1,479,062.

His earnings have come from both large and small rodeos, with a focus on accumulating points based on his monetary winnings.

In 2022, Aus ended the season eighth in the world standings, earning $206,851. He also earned $119,897 during the regular season.

Some of his notable earnings include $11,500 at The Calgary Stampede and nearly $80,000 at the Wrangler National Championship Rodeo event in Las Vegas. In 2020, Aus finished in eighth place with earnings topping the $170,000 mark.

At the NFR alone, he earned just over $91,000 that year. These figures demonstrate Aus’s consistent performance and success in the rodeo circuit.

Endorsements

Tanner Aus has received support from various sponsors throughout his career, including Midwest Agri, Salty Dog Sister Boutique, Granite Falls Dairy Queen, Jug Waterers, Carroll Spur Co., Phoenix Performance Products, and Wrangler.

Personal Details

Wife

Tanner Aus is married to Lonissa Aus. The couple got married on October 15, 2016. They have three children together.

How Old is Tanner Aus?

Tanner Aus is approximately 33 years old, as he was born in 1990.

What is his nationality?

He is an American citizen.
